docs.lead_paragraph: TAIPEI, Taiwan, March 27 -A sharp rise in the number of teen-agers on Taiwan has temporarily set back efforts to reduce the rate of population growth.

headline.main: BIRTH-CURB DRIVE SLOWS ON TAIWAN; Trend Reversed by Big Rise in Teen-Age Marriages
